alternatives.transcript: Software as a Service is hands down the best business model in the world. But starting a SaaS business is really, really hard. Over the last 14 years of running MicroConf, I've met so many developers and entrepreneurs who dream of launching their own software business, but they just weren't sure where to start. Or maybe they did get started and they spent 6 months in their basement toiling away at an incredibly well engineered V1 of their app only to launch to crickets because the solution they built solved the problem that no one actually needed solving. That's why I've created the SaaS Launchpad. In this course, I've pulled together all of my strategies, tactics, and frameworks to help you find a great SaaS idea and turn it into a real business with real customers who are paying you real money. I'm Rob Walling, an author and serial entrepreneur. I've built 6 companies, including Drip, which I sold for a life changing sum of money in 2016. Now I run MicroConf and TinySeed, which is the first startup accelerator designed for bootstrappers. Through 730 podcast episodes, dozens of in person conferences, and investing in over 190 SaaS companies, I've interacted with thousands of startup founders. I've seen what it takes to be successful in SaaS, and I've seen over and over what causes startups to fail. I put everything I know about launching a SaaS into this course. I'm really excited to share my hard fought and often painful lessons with you. If you've dreamed of launching your own software business but aren't sure where to start, this course is for you. Whether you're a first time founder or a seasoned entrepreneur looking to venture into the SaaS space, the SaaS Launchpad will give you the knowledge, the strategies, and the frameworks you need to transform your vision into a thriving business. With over 9 hours of content across 27 modules, the SaaS Launchpad is crammed with in-depth lessons that will help you on your journey from idea generation to product launch and your first paying customers. The course is broken up into 3 phases, starting with the idea phase. In it, there are modules on the ingredients that make a great SaaS idea, how to find a real problem that people are willing to pay to solve, and my 2, 2,200 framework for idea validation. Then in the build phase, we look at creating and launching a successful MVP, what it takes to create a landing page that converts, and how to think about early stage marketing. In the launch phase, we cover building and launching to your early access list, iterating to get to product market fit, and the right way to price your SaaS. Additionally, I brought in some of the best minds I know to talk to you about what's working right now. Jason Buckingham talks with me about how he made nearly 100 cold calls in order to find a 7 figure SaaS idea. Ross Hudgins lets you look over his shoulder as he explores SEO opportunities for a new SaaS idea, and Craig Hewitt gives a masterclass on sales for early stage founders. I'm so confident in the value of this course that I'm offering a 30 day no questions asked money back guarantee. Looking forward to seeing you on the inside.
